	<A HREF="
https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus:text:1999.01.0160:book=1:chapter=25
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Pausanias,WIDTH,220)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Pausanias, 1.25.3‑5</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note38" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref38
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">38</A>
Cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17F*.html#109
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Book 17.109.1</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note39" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref39
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">39</A>
In 324, the year before Alexander's death.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note40" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref40
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">40</A>
The games began with a contest of heralds, the winner in which officiated throughout the festival. Cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Nero*.html#24
	"TARGET="Suetonius_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EPlusL,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Suetonius, <I>Nero</I>, 24.1</A>;
	<A HREF="
https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus:text:1999.01.0160:book=5:chapter=22
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Pausanias,WIDTH,220)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Pausanias, 5.22.1
	</A>
and J. G. Frazer on this passage.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
