<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note56" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref56
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">56</A>
We have no account of the immediate sequel. Seuthes retained his title, but seems to have become an unwilling ally of Lysimachus, whom he deserted in 313
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19E*.html#73.8
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Book 19.73.8)</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note57" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref57
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">57</A>
<I>i.e.</I> of Lamia
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#13.6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(chap. 13.6)</A>, which had continued through the winter of 323/2. Melitia is north of Lamia in southern Thessaly.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note58" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref58
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">58</A>
Cp. Arrian, <I>FGrH</I>, 156.1.9;
	<A HREF="
https://www.forumromanum.org/literature/justin/texte13.html#5
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2PlusTranslation,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Justin, 13.5.14‑16</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note59" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref59
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">59</A>
Diodorus has condensed his account of the naval campaign to the point of unintelligibility, although it was probably the decisive factor in the war. We cannot even be sure whether Diodorus intends to mention two sea battles or three. T. Walek (<I>Revue de Philologie</I>, 48 (1924), 23 ff.) reconstructs the campaign as follows. While part of the original Athenian fleet of 240 ships
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#10.2
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(chap. 10.2)
	</A>
blockaded the fleet of Antipater in the Malian Gulf, the rest held the Hellespont and for a time prevented Leonnatus from coming to the aid of


<A ID="p57x"></A>Antipater. Although this fleet was increased to 170 ships, it was defeated in the spring of 322 by the larger fleet of Cleitus at Abydos (cp. <I>Inscriptiones Graecae</I>, editio minor, 2.298 and 493). Cleitus then crossed the Aegean and defeated the other Athenian fleet with great loss at the Lichades Islands in the Malian Gulf (see critical note), and at once removed to Amorgos for the final battle (<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Demetrius*.html#11.3
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Plutarch, <I>Demetrius</I>, 11.3</A>; <I>Marmor Parium</I> for 323/2), which ended Athenian sea power forever. It is hard to see how any battle of this war could have taken place near the Echinades (off the west coast of Acarnania), but this name may conceal a reference to Echinus on the north shore of the Malian Gulf.

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
	<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify small italic">
The critical note to the Greek text of §9 (<SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">περὶ τὰς καλουμένας Ἔχινάδας νήσους</SPAN>) reads:
	<P CLASS="i1 b0 a0 justify">
Grauert suggests <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">Λιχάδας</SPAN> for <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">Ἔχινάδας</SPAN> (see note to translation).
	</P></DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="6" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref60
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">60</A>
According to Hieronymus of Cardia (<I>FGrH</I>, 154.4), Ariarathes lived to the age of <SPAN CLASS="whole">eighty-two</SPAN>. For this campaign cp. Arrian, <I>FGrH</I>, 156.1.11;
	<A HREF="
https://www.forumromanum.org/literature/justin/texte13.html#6
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2PlusTranslation,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Justin, 13.6.1‑3</A>; Plutarch, <I>Eumenes</I>, 3.<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Eumenes*.html#3.2
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
