(2.33.4)</A>, Harpalus was murdered either by his slaves or by a Macedonian named Pausanias. For other accounts of Thibron's campaign against Cyrenê and his final defeat by Ptolemy cp. Arrian, <I>FGrH</I>, 156.9.16‑19;
	<A HREF="
https://www.forumromanum.org/literature/justin/texte13.html#6
	"TARGET="offsite"
