"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Book 17.108.6
	</A>
and in Arrian the number of mercenaries is given as six thousand.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note71" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref71
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">71</A>
Also called Hesperides, Euhesperides, and Berenicê


<A ID="p71x"></A>(modern Benghazi), the westernmost city of Cyrenê. Barca lies a short distance north-east.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note72" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref72
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">72</A>
<I>i.e.</I> against the Cyrenians and their Libyan and Carthaginian army, who are not mentioned until
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#21.4
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
chap. 21.4</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note73" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref73
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">73</A>
The capture of Cyrenê is placed in 322/1 by the Parian Marble. Ptolemy had not yet become king
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/20C*.html#53.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Book 20.53.3)</A>. For the later attempt of the Cyrenians to recover their freedom see
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19E*.html#79
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Book 19.79.1‑3</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note74" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref74
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">74</A>
Cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#16.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">chap. 16.3</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note75" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref75
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">75</A>
Justin
	<A HREF="
https://www.forumromanum.org/literature/justin/texte13.html#6
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2PlusTranslation,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(13.6.1‑3)
	</A>
tells much the same tale but in connection with Perdiccas' war against Ariarathes.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note76" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref76
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">76</A>
For these and other intrigues, and for the flight of Antigonus to Macedonia, cp. Arrian, <I>FGrH</I>, 156.9.20‑24, 26;


<A ID="p81x"></A><A HREF="
https://www.forumromanum.org/literature/justin/texte13.html#6
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2PlusTranslation,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Justin, 13.6.4‑8</A>. The flight cannot be dated before the winter of 322/1.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note77" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref77
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">77</A>
Cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#18.8
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">chap. 18.8</A>. This campaign, since it follows the battle of Crannon (September, 322), belongs to the archon-year 322/1.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note78" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref78
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">78</A>
The winter of 322/1.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note79" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#ref79
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">79</A>
Cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18B*.html#29
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">chaps. 29‑32
	</A>
for the campaign of Eumenes, and
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18B*.html#33
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
chaps. 33‑37
	</A>
for that of Perdiccas.



